################################################################################
### This file use the following template format:
### - Lines starting with “#” are template syntax:
###   - Comments are introduced using “###”, as illustrated in the current line.
###   - The second character of the line is ignored.
###   - The rest of the line is interpreted as Python syntax.
###   - Indentation is 4 spaces.
###   - Indented blocks of code must be terminated by the corresponding
###     “endXXX” instruction, e.g.:
###
###         if a:
###             ...
###         else:
###             ...
###         endif
###
### - Lines not starting with “#” are interpreted as a Python f-strings.
###
###   Whenever possible, prefer using layout *ranges* than layout indexes, such
###   as: `single`, `first`, `later` and `any`. They are documented at:
###   https://xkbcommon.org/doc/current/rule-file-format.html#grammar
###   They will be converted to the appropriate syntax when rendering in the
###   legacy format.
################################################################################
